==Sociological stimuli==

On average, lesbians tend to not get as much education as gay males, and earn much less than gay males. (continue) {{fact}}

Lesbians's needs and choices can cause parents to withdraw financial and emotional support.  This often causes hopes for college to disappear.  (continue) {{fact}}

A woman making minimum wage may not be able to afford more than a garage apartment or a rented room, but two can pool their incomes and have an easier life together.  (continue)  {{fact}}

The gay bar culture scene is still considered the primary venue for meeting potential partners.   Bars mean alcohol and that poses a huge problem problematic because lesbians, like gay males, have a high incidence of chemical addictions, surpassing the rate found in heterosexuals.  (continue) {{fact}}


